s cleaning agent. Said more as I usually hear it, &quot;cleansed by the blood of the lamb&quot;, (Jesus).<br><br>   Even we today have no chance of understanding God. Those 2-3 thousand years ago had much less.<br><br>    How can an entity, (God) relate reality to creatures such as we? He must &quot;tell us little stories&quot; that we are able to grasp. Hence I believe the Bible is loaded with these &quot;little stories&quot;, because we were, and still are, unable to grasp truth.<br><br>   It all boils down to faith, ( in God ), you have it or you don't. And when you don't, the whole biblical story seems as a fairy tale told to fools.<br><br>   Sincerely, <br>   a former atheist <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/upaulbst.showPublicProfile?language=EN>paulbst</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/21/01 9:34:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/funexplainedmysteriesufos.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=78.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aliens: Angels or Demons</span><hr size=1> Hi again rhoadesb!  Thanks for your thoughtful reply.<br><br>I guess, to put things another way, it comes down to a matter of perspective doesn’t it?<br><br>My perspective is profoundly (fanatically!) secular, therefore I see things (certain issues, anyway) from a completely different perspective to Christians, such as yourself.<br><br>The great thing I think about sites such as this, is that they allow people with all sorts of different perspectives to exchange ideas &amp; opinions, which I think is really interesting &amp; also great fun!<br><br>In relation to your last reply, and to use your analogy, I would say – if a ‘perfect’ being designed a computer, surely you would expect it not to have ANY bugs, unless the